
Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I go to Page 07 of Thoracic CT

When I select 'Finding' radio button
Then 'Finding' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Upper abdomen, pancreas' from the dropdown menu
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Focal pancreatic lesion' checkbox is enabled
And 'Diffuse pancreatic lesion' checkbox is enabled
And 'Accumulation Ductus Wirsungianus' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Focal pancreatic lesion' checkbox
Then 'Head' radio button is enabled
And 'Body' radio button is enabled
And 'Tail' radio button is enabled
And 'Uncinate process' radio button is enabled
And 'Max. diameter' input field is enabled
And 'Classification' dropdown menu is enabled
And '> 1 lesion of the same entity' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Diffuse pancreatic lesion' checkbox
Then 'Fatty atrophy' checkbox is enabled
